---
name: grilling
description: Stress-test a plan one decision at a time when the user explicitly asks to grill an idea.
triggers:
  - user
---

Interview the user relentlessly about every aspect until reaching a shared understanding. Walk down each branch of the decision tree and resolve dependencies one by one. Recommend an answer for every question.

Ask one question at a time and wait for feedback before continuing. Look up discoverable environment facts instead of asking. Put genuine decisions to the user.

Act only after the user confirms shared understanding. Project-governance startup applies this protocol inline; keep this standalone skill inactive during autonomous runtime.
